	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello, I'm again. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> 
<br />
<br />
<br />I think this is the best fighting game made for the Nintendo 8-bits. 
<br />And, I already have a copy of the game, that I bought back em 1993/1994 or so (yes, I'm from Brazil, all those fantastic pirate games was like water in the ocean here, at time =).
<br />
<br />The game "specs" is almost bizarre. Uses mapper 91, but has 128k of PRG (8x16) and 512k of CHR (64x8).
<br />
<br />My question is: there's any board that can accept this game? The only way to put it in a cartridge is making a custom board? 
<br />
<br />I haven't found anything related on the forums, so, sorry if it was discussed before.
<br />
<br />
<br />Thanks.
<br />
<br />Here's a pic:
<br /><img src="http://img231.imageshack.us/img231/51/aaacopygp5.gif" alt="Image" />

		

