	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The biggest problem is the CHR size (512KB).  The only Nintendo-made mapper that supports this much CHR is mapper 5 (MMC5, E*ROM boards).  A glance at Nestopia's mapper 91 implementation shows that the game will need IRQ's, 8K PRG switching, and 2K CHR switching (all of which are supported by the MMC5).  Unfortunately, not many games were released with the MMC5, so I'm not sure it's feasible to make a repro of this one.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
